properties.name: American Museum of Natural History
properties.description: Posted by Synergy161  Central Park West at 79th Street, New York, NYThe juggernaut of natural history museums. As a kid I loved the dinosaurs and the giant blue whale. As a so-called-adult, I STILL love the dinos and the whale. But there are also gem stones bigger than my fist, meteorites, and other way cool stuff.

properties.name: Batdorf and Bronson
properties.description: Posted by Synergy161  516 Capitol Way S. Olympia, WA 98501 The finest coffee house in Olympia. Straight-up black coffee is fairly bitter schwag, but mochas and similar drinks are made with primo Ghirardelli chocolate and Monin syrups. The best thing about this place is the place itself. An immense cafe with vaulted ceilings, seriously comfy seating, a cozy fireplace, free wi-fi internet (nicely provided by Zhonka), and some of the best people-watching around.

properties.name: Burger House
properties.description: Posted by Synergy161  6913 Hillcrest Ave. Dallas, TX 75205A Dallas classic. For over 50 years, these guys have been slingin\' some of the most bitchin\' burgers around and their seasoned salt takes their fries into a whole other realm of fantastic fry-ness. Just be sure to swing by an ATM first or have cash on hand. (I always forget that they don\'t take plastic.)

properties.name: Central Grocery
properties.description: Posted by Synergy161 923 Decatur St. New Orleans, LAThe birthplace of the muffuletta, one of the finest sandwich creations in the world. This place did it first and still does it the best. When visiting New Orleans, a stop here is required. Never mind the lines of people. It\'s worth it.

properties.name: Eatzi's
properties.description: Posted by Synergy161 3403 Oak Lawn Ave Dallas, TX 75219This place takes food and makes it all that it can be. I really wish that they would open a location in Seattle, so that I could go more than the once or twice a year that I make it back to Dallas. They still make the best (and cheapest) caesar salad that I\'ve ever had. An absolute must for any food lover.

properties.name: FAO Schwarz
properties.description: Posted by Synergy161  767 Fifth Avenue New York, NY 10153If you ever find yourself in Manhattan with some time to kill, swing by FAO Schwarz. It may or may not be the world\'s largest toy store, but, either way, it is quite awe inspiring. I am and have always been a kid at heart, and this monument to toys always makes me smile.

properties.name: Goose Cove Lodge
properties.description: Posted by Synergy161 300 Goose Cove Rd. (P.O. Box 40) Sunset, ME 04683My first taste of the true northeast. My family and I made a few trips up here to Deer Isle, Stonington, and Penobscot Bay. If I didn\'t live in Olympia, I would hope that I could live in this area. Lobster, crab rolls, and some of the most beautiful scenery anywhere.

properties.name: Health Camp
properties.description: Posted by Synergy161 2601 Circle Rd, Waco, TX 76701When driving past Waco on Interstate 35, one must time his trip so that his approach to Health Camp coincides with the peak of his hunger. When one is at his hungriest, the greasy, salty, sweet goodness that is found here can be likened to ambrosia for the gods.

properties.name: Highland Park Pharmacy
properties.description: Posted by Synergy161   3229 Knox St, Dallas, TX 75205This place is definitely one of the top ten things that I miss most about living in Dallas. I was a faithful customer for close to 20 years and still make sure to go every time I\'m back in Big D. Monster milkshakes, sinful sodas, frosty freezes, great grilled cheese, chew-tastic chicken salad, and pimped-out pimiento cheese. \'nuff said.

properties.name: Hyer Hall
properties.description: Posted by Synergy1616424 Hilltop Lane Dallas, TX 7520514 years ago, I began my pubescent college career here. I took Introduction to Logic taught by a Dr. David Ring. I also met my first girlfriend here and told her that I loved her while sitting on the stone bench outside. ah, memories.

properties.name: Lake Mancos Ranch
properties.description: Posted by Synergy16142688 County Road N Mancos, CO 81328As a kid, growing up in the hella hot hotness that is Dallas in the summer time, this place was the refuge from the city heat that my family and I fled to. We relaxed, played cards, rode horses, ate great home cooking, and tried to imagine that we actually lived there. Even if I never have a family of my own, I hope to get back there someday.

properties.name: Lettermen Hall
properties.description: Posted by Synergy1613115 Binkley Ave Dallas, TX 75205I spent my first fantastically unimpressive official year (\'94-\'95) of my college career living here. My roommate Theo Stanley and friend Cynthia-Anne Krempetz have since gotten married and had a beautiful baby. Rachael Johnson, Cameron Cobb, Susie Dodge, Shawn Chou, Monique Hitchings, and Brian Torrey Scott are all great friends that I have lost touch with. My friend, Mike Aronov, has even been on several episodes of my favorite TV addiction, Law and Order (One episode of Law & Order: Prime, two episodes of Law & Order: SVU, and the very first episode of Law & Order: CI). Hella cool.

properties.name: Mont Parnasse Diner
properties.description: Posted by Synergy161 824 Central Park Ave, Scarsdale, NYWhenever I used to get over to see my family in New York at Thanksgiving, this swell little diner was an inevitable stop at least once during my visit. Fairly cheap, but still hella good. Great reubens and open til 2:00 AM.

properties.name: Peggy Sue BBQ
properties.description: Posted by Synergy161 6600 Snider Plz. Dallas, TX 75205I would say that this is the second best BBQ in Dallas. Granted, I haven\'t lived in Dallas for almost seven years, but from my 22 years of experience as a Dallasite, I stand by my rating. For any SMU student or University Park resident, this is the best and definitely the most convenient. Great smoked meats, tangy sauce, classic cobblers, and one-of-a-kind fried pies.

properties.name: Ralph's Thriftway
properties.description: Posted by Synergy161  1908 4th Ave E. Olympia, WA 98506I will whole-heartedly admit that the Stormans people who run the two Olympia area Thriftways are über conservative right-wing fundamentalist Christian demon-spawn, but this has still become my most frequent stop for supplies for everyday life. Not only is it within easy walking distance of my house, but there are super friendly employees, bitchin\' baked goods, wicked good wines, tasty Chinese food choices, and even a Subway sandwich shop.

properties.name: Red Top BBQ
properties.description: Posted by Synergy161913 Capitol Way S. Olympia, WA 98501For a native of Dallas, TX, transplantation to Olympia, WA involved considerable shock - cultural, political, and gastronomical. I do get back to Big D at least once a year for a week or so to catch up with family, friends, and my favorite foods, but while I\'m living 1700 miles from where I grew up, Red Top BBQ keeps me satiated and satisfied. Outstanding smoked meats (pork, chicken, sausage, and ribs), tangy, spicy sauce, and healthy Texas-sized portions.

properties.name: Sand Castle Drive-In
properties.description: Posted by Synergy161 788 Point Brown Avenue NE, Ocean Shores, WA 98569Granted, the GoogleMap hasn\'t mapped Ocean Shores yet, but that doesn\'t mean that it isn\'t a cool place to be. And if you are cool enough to find yourself here, you\'ve just gotta go to the Sand Castle. I can\'t remember what the GIGANTIC fried seafood platter is called, but it needs to be experienced to be believed.

properties.name: Shakespeare-in-the-Park (Samuell-Grand Park)
properties.description: Posted by Synergy161   1500 Tenison Dallas, TX 75223I had my first REAL kiss here 17 summers ago. If you\'re a native Dallasite and have never been to a Shakepeare-in-the-Park production, you owe it to yourself. A great, romantic date on a warm summer evening.

properties.name: Sonny Bryan's Smokehouse
properties.description: Posted by Synergy1612202 Inwood Rd. Dallas, TX 75235The BEST BBQ in Dallas. For almost 100 years. Period.

properties.name: Starbucks (College & Yelm, Store 3247)
properties.description: Posted by Synergy161 4660 Whitman Lane SE Lacey, WA 98503There are many Starbucks, but this one is mine.
